"{\"abstract\":\"Rigid structure-from-motion (RSfM) and non-rigid structure-from-motion (NRSfM) have long been treated in the literature as separate (different) problems. Inspired by a previous work which solved directly for 3D scene structure by factoring the relative camera poses out, we revisit the principle of \\u201cmaximizing rigidity\\u201d in structure-from-motion literature, and develop a unified theory which is applicable to both rigid and non-rigid structure reconstruction in a rigidity-agnostic way. We formulate these problems as a convex semi-definite program, imposing constraints that seek to apply the principle of minimizing non-rigidity. Our results demonstrate the efficacy of the approach, with stateof- the-art accuracy on various 3D reconstruction problems.\",\"arxivId\":\"1707.05009\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"50478588\",\"name\":\"P. Ji\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/50478588\"},{\"authorId\":\"40124570\",\"name\":\"Hongdong Li\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/40124570\"},{\"authorId\":\"1681554\",\"name\":\"Yuchao Dai\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1681554\"},{\"authorId\":\"145950884\",\"name\":\"I. Reid\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145950884\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3380804\",\"name\":\"Shaifali Parashar\"},{\"authorId\":\"2862871\",\"name\":\"M. Salzmann\"},{\"authorId\":\"153918727\",\"name\":\"P. Fua\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/cvpr42600.2020.00213\",\"intent\":[\"methodology\",\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"39cc401cb5dfe983c3e967f3d7e549c656e3da52\",\"title\":\"Local Non-Rigid Structure-From-Motion From Diffeomorphic Mappings\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/39cc401cb5dfe983c3e967f3d7e549c656e3da52\",\"venue\":\"2020 IEEE/CVF Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (CVPR)\",\"year\":2020},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2409281\",\"n